Martin Advances to Quarterfinals 
Top-seeded Todd Martin advanced to the quarterfinals of the MassMutual
Tennis Championships with a 7-6 (7-3), 6-1 victory over Byron Black of
Zimbabwe.
Martin, an American, was broken in the first game before getting even
at 1-1 when Black double faulted. Both held serve the rest of the set
until Martin took control in the tie-breaker.
The lone upset of the day came when Jonas Bjorkman of Sweden defeated
No. 4 seed Patrick Rafter of Australia 6-2, 6-3. Bjorkman will face
Australia's Mark Philippoussis, who defeated Russia's Andrei Chesnokov
6-4, 6-3.
Germany's Carsten Arriens rallied to beat Michael Tebbutt of Australia
2-6, 6-3, 6-3 and will play Martin in Friday's quarterfinals.
